== Geography == === Geological ===
The Bay is bisected by the Swan Islands fault, where the North American and Caribbean plates meet.{{sfn|Bundschuh|Alvarado|2012|p=3|loc=fig. 1.1}} Its climate is broadly tropical, with a May{{nbnd}}October wet season, and a November{{nbnd}}April dry season.{{sfn|Bundschuh|Alvarado|2012|pp=2-6|loc=sec. 1.2.1.1}} It is subject to Atlantic hurricanes, most especially during June{{nbnd}}September.{{sfn|Bundschuh|Alvarado|2012|pp=2-6|loc=sec. 1.2.1.1}}
The northeastern coast of the Bay (ie northern Belize and southern Quintana Roo) forms part of the Yucatan Peninsula, a vast karstic or carbonate platform.{{sfn|Bunschuh|Alvarado|2012|pp=81-82|loc=sec. 3.2.2}}{{sfn|Bunschuh|Alvarado|2012|p=77|loc=fig. 3.1}} This coast is characterised by broad brackish lagoons, mangrove swamps, and seasonally-flooded marshes.{{sfn|Bunschuh|Alvarado|2012|pp=81-82|loc=sec. 3.2.2}} Its waters are dotted with fringing reefs and coral cayes<!-- not "cays" nor "keys", per Belizean spelling-->.{{sfn|Bunschuh|Alvarado|2012|pp=81-82|loc=sec. 3.2.2}}
The southeastern coast of the Bay (ie southern Belize) forms part of the Mayan highlands, a series of distinct mountain ranges extending in an arc from xxx.{{sfn|Bunschuh|Alvarado|2012|p=77|loc=fig. 3.1}}
The mouth of the Bay (ie Amatique Bay) forms part of the Motagua fault zone, xxx.{{sfn|Bunschuh|Alvarado|2012|p=77|loc=fig. 3.1}}
The southern coast of the Bay (ie xxx) forms part of the Chortis highlands, xxx.{{sfn|Bunschuh|Alvarado|2012|p=77|loc=fig. 3.1}}
